# Project Structure Guide

The main source code is located in the [`src`](mdc:src) directory. Here are the key subdirectories and their purposes:

- [`components`](mdc:src/components): Contains reusable UI components, organized into feature- or type-specific subfolders (e.g., [`cards`](mdc:src/components/cards), [`coin-icon`](mdc:src/components/coin-icon), [`navbar`](mdc:src/components/navbar)). Example files: [`FeesPanel.tsx`](mdc:src/components/FeesPanel.tsx), [`DropdownMenu.tsx`](mdc:src/components/DropdownMenu.tsx).
- [`screens`](mdc:src/screens): Contains top-level app screens and flows, often grouped by feature or section (e.g., [`Airdrops`](mdc:src/screens/Airdrops), [`transaction-details`](mdc:src/screens/transaction-details)). Example files: [`SendSheet.tsx`](mdc:src/screens/SendSheet.tsx), [`ProfileScreen.tsx`](mdc:src/screens/ProfileScreen.tsx).
- [`state`](mdc:src/state): Manages application state, with subfolders for different domains (e.g., [`assets`](mdc:src/state/assets), [`wallets`](mdc:src/state/wallets), [`navigation`](mdc:src/state/navigation)).
- [`utils`](mdc:src/utils): Utility functions and helpers used throughout the codebase. Example files: [`ethereumUtils.ts`](mdc:src/utils/ethereumUtils.ts), [`formatDate.ts`](mdc:src/utils/formatDate.ts).

Other notable directories include [`hooks`](mdc:src/hooks) (custom React hooks), [`redux`](mdc:src/redux) (Redux logic), [`assets`](mdc:src/assets) (static assets), and [`config`](mdc:src/config) (configuration files).

The main entry point for the app is typically [`App.tsx`](mdc:src/App.tsx).
